  <!-- Plasteel Golem - New, tougher variant -->
  <ThingDef ParentName="MOL_BaseGolem">
    <defName>MOL_Golem_Plasteel</defName>
    <label>plasteel golem</label>
    <description>Plasteel formations exhibiting dangerous temporary animation. How such advanced composite material came to possess psychoreactive properties is hotly debated - did archotechs influence plasteel's original development, or did later contamination affect already-refined deposits? The constructs are nearly indestructible during active episodes, then simply become inert plasteel again. Like sanguophages and psylink neuroformers, they're another mystery left by incomprehensible minds.</description>
    <statBases>
      <MoveSpeed>4.2</MoveSpeed>
      <ArmorRating_Blunt>0.55</ArmorRating_Blunt>
      <ArmorRating_Sharp>1.0</ArmorRating_Sharp>
      <PsychicSensitivity>0.25</PsychicSensitivity>
    </statBases>
    <tools>
